1
00:00:16,870 --> 00:00:17,850
Who are you?

2
00:00:18,330 --> 00:00:19,780
Where is my master,

3
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:20,800
Zhang Haiqi?

4
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:22,280
She's dead too.

5
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,300
Everyone but us

6
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:26,760
died.

7
00:00:26,910 --> 00:00:27,640
Impossible.

8
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,760
Do you know how strong she is?

9
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,720
Why would all the people you know

10
00:00:33,770 --> 00:00:35,450
be the favored ones?

11
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:38,250
Isn't Zhang Haixia dead too?

12
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:41,790
Mr. Zhang,

13
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,380
the Archives is long gone.

14
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,200
She's already dead.

15
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,460
What's the point of

16
00:00:49,460 --> 00:00:51,260
trying to get to the bottom of it?

17
00:00:53,570 --> 00:00:54,250
Leave.

18
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,540
No one will blame you anymore.

19
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:02,480
No one will care about you anymore either.

20
00:01:32,650 --> 00:01:34,110
The people in the Archives

21
00:01:34,289 --> 00:01:37,220
are to be buried
by a higher-level agent after death.

22
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,660
You're a low-level agent.

23
00:01:39,759 --> 00:01:40,890
Strictly speaking,

24
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:44,479
low-level agents are not considered
to be from the Archives.

25
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,940
I'm afraid you haven't even

26
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:47,400
been in the real Archives.

27
00:02:00,540 --> 00:02:02,230
You can take him away.

28
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:04,400
Bury him wherever you want.

29
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:07,150
What else can you do for him?

30
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:15,120
[Zhang Haiqi] [Zhang Haixia]
[Zhang Hailou]

31
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,630
[Zhang Haiqi] [Zhang Haixia]
[Zhang Hailou]

32
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,500
[Zhang Haixia]

33
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,140
You can take him away.

34
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:21,220
Bury him wherever you want.

35
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:24,150
What else can you do for him?

36
00:04:24,230 --> 00:04:26,650
[Zhang Haiqi] [Zhang Haixia]

37
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:36,240
Mo Yungao put Twilight Grass in Nanyang.

38
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,450
He then brought it back

39
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:39,250
to Xiacheng through the Nan'an.

40
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:43,420
[Urgent]

41
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:41,620
What's his next plan?

42
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:47,159
I'm sorry,

43
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,280
[Zhang Haixia]

44
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,070
Haixia.

45
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:50,070
I have to do this.

46
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:58,530
[Zhang Haiqi] [Zhang Haixia]
[Zhang Hailou]

47
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:04,170
Zhang Hailou, Zhang Hailou.

48
00:05:05,690 --> 00:05:08,290
How did my student, you,
turn out to be trouble?

49
00:05:10,850 --> 00:05:12,700
I'll give you another chance.

50
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:15,230
As for what fate awaits the two of you,

51
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:19,330
that depends on whether you can
overcome your true nature.

52
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:59,380
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

53
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,380
[Episode 12]

54
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,250
The night tide is ebbs slow.

55
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,330
We didn't find anything.

56
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:10,100
Yeah.

57
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,850
Why is there someone there?

58
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,380
What...

59
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,160
Take a fire statement to light it.

60
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,220
Are they refugees?

61
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:37,659
[Assassin, Bai Zhu]

62
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:35,570
Sir.

63
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:48,380
[Lu Junxiang, Adjutant
in the Mo Warlord Faction of Beilian]

64
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,460
I need to know

65
00:07:48,890 --> 00:07:50,690
the situation of the Nan'an.

66
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:57,330
Please

67
00:07:58,210 --> 00:07:59,760
promise me one thing first.

68
00:08:03,410 --> 00:08:04,600
Say it.

69
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,700
I want to see Bai Yu.

70
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,580
Sure.

71
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:24,100
Our mission to assassinate

72
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,500
people of the Archives in Nanyang

73
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:29,300
successfully wiped out
32 people of the Archives.

74
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:32,350
Most of them were poisoned
by Twilight Grass Poison.

75
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,909
But unexpectedly,

76
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,840
there were survivors.

77
00:08:36,530 --> 00:08:38,340
They seem to have antibodies.

78
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:41,690
The Twilight Grass Poison can't kill them.

79
00:08:41,789 --> 00:08:43,809
It can only make them hallucinate.

80
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,450
I've submitted the report.

81
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,170
On top of that,

82
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:49,100
the director of the Archives,

83
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,390
Zhang Haiqi...

84
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:53,770
appeared on the Nan'an.

85
00:08:56,610 --> 00:08:58,810
She boarded the boat
as the daughter of the Ship King.

86
00:08:58,810 --> 00:09:00,370
Because of her counterattack,

87
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:01,960
all the people we sent

88
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,080
were killed.

89
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,450
Only I survived.

90
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:06,790
We seldom had the chance

91
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:08,370
to get close to each other.

92
00:09:08,370 --> 00:09:10,430
Zhang Haiqi has arrived in Xiacheng.

93
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:11,910
Sorry.

94
00:09:20,170 --> 00:09:22,250
You finally showed up.

95
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:31,470
Sir, I want to see Bai Yu.

96
00:09:31,490 --> 00:09:32,660
Take me to Bai Yu!

97
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:34,110
Let me see her!

98
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:57,580
She appeared.

99
00:09:58,260 --> 00:09:59,300
She appeared!

100
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,160
Where is my medicine?

101
00:10:09,410 --> 00:10:11,160
Get ready.

102
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,460
To the Dong Residence.

103
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:22,260
[A place derives glory
from its illustrious sons]

104
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:53,460
Let's go.

105
00:10:53,910 --> 00:10:55,520
Who buys a coffin on tab?

106
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:57,000
On the dead person's tab
on top of that?

107
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,800
If you don't have money, just go.

108
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,150
I'll trade for it with this.

109
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,210
He's pulling two coffins.

110
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,610
Stop looking.

111
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:43,580
Zhang Hailou.

112
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:52,750
Miss Dong?

113
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:00,330
Master!

114
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:03,830
Miss Dong,

115
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,550
are you really my master?

116
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,030
I knew it...

117
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:15,720
Master.

118
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:17,870
Master.

119
00:13:18,570 --> 00:13:19,580
Master.

120
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:20,940
Master.

121
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:31,590
Zhang Hailou.

122
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,410
Ever having you as my student

123
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:36,790
is the most humiliating thing in my life.

124
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:39,440
I should have drowned you in the sea.

125
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:42,160
So many things wouldn't have happened.

126
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,660
The higher-ups are right.

127
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,680
People like you shouldn't be kept.

128
00:13:59,070 --> 00:13:59,770
Master.

129
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:01,530
I know...

130
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:05,610
you blame me for killing Shrimpie

131
00:14:06,530 --> 00:14:07,910
and harming the Archives.

132
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,440
That's why you're mad at me.

133
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:12,330
Mentor!

134
00:14:13,110 --> 00:14:13,980
Just kill me.

135
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,220
Kill me!

136
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,150
Kill me!

137
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:18,960
Kill you?

138
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:20,790
If I kill you,

139
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:22,790
will Zhang Haixia come back to life?

140
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,860
Will the people
from the Archives come back to life?

141
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:33,960
Master...

142
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:36,440
Master...

143
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:38,790
All these years,

144
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:41,050
so many things happened in the Archives—

145
00:14:41,460 --> 00:14:43,370
why didn't you send me a telegram?

146
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,200
Zhang Haixia is higher ranked than you.

147
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,740
He knows everything,

148
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,480
yet you don't know?

149
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:53,500
You should ask him why.

150
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,560
Master.

151
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:55,910
I know I was wrong.

152
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,400
Back then in Panhua Reef,

153
00:15:00,580 --> 00:15:01,710
If it weren't for me,

154
00:15:01,790 --> 00:15:03,990
Shrimpie wouldn't have been disabled.

155
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:06,620
I know I was wrong.

156
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,590
So he knew...

157
00:15:18,290 --> 00:15:19,340
But he didn't tell me

158
00:15:19,340 --> 00:15:20,370
to protect me.

159
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,140
All these years,

160
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,000
how many things has he not told me

161
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:27,660
to protect me?

162
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:31,520
Why didn't I know until now?

163
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,570
Master.

164
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:37,840
You knew

165
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,650
I would kill Zhang Haixia, right?

166
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:40,340
Master,

167
00:15:40,530 --> 00:15:42,960
you told me again and again
to overcome my true nature.

168
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,060
But I realized it too late.

169
00:15:45,870 --> 00:15:47,650
It's too late...

170
00:15:50,790 --> 00:15:51,620
Why did you...

171
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,950
Why did you let him

172
00:15:53,980 --> 00:15:55,290
go to Nanyang with me?

173
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:57,170
Why did you watch him

174
00:15:57,190 --> 00:15:58,270
die because of me?

175
00:15:58,530 --> 00:16:00,080
You knew I am...

176
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,620
I am such a person.

177
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:02,470
Why did you...

178
00:16:02,790 --> 00:16:04,510
Why did you bring me back

179
00:16:04,540 --> 00:16:05,640
and not let me die?

180
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,100
Are you done?

181
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:26,650
Master, I know I was wrong.

182
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:28,920
Bodhisattva fears karma.

183
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:31,280
A man fears the consequences.

184
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:34,200
You chose to be a man

185
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,720
because you didn't pay a big enough price.

186
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:38,710
Now, if you want good results,

187
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,020
you need to start sowing karma.

188
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:42,700
Remember,

189
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,530
no one in this world will help you

190
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:48,300
like Zhang Haixia.

191
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:00,620
I know.

192
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:02,760
Master.

193
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:15,780
Although committing suicide
is a cheap move,

194
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,510
you have more conscience
than I thought.

195
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,579
Since you have the guts to die,

196
00:17:21,660 --> 00:17:23,859
why don't you die a more valuable death?

197
00:17:24,069 --> 00:17:25,790
Think with your brain.

198
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,790
Zhang Haixia's a smart man.

199
00:17:29,330 --> 00:17:31,590
Why would he wait for someone to kill him?

200
00:17:34,770 --> 00:17:36,170
What do you mean, Master?

201
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:41,070
I checked all his vitals.

202
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,220
He's dead.

203
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:49,100
There is a very special way
to save his life.

204
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,370
Only a few people in the Archives know it.

205
00:17:56,110 --> 00:17:56,570
Master...

206
00:17:56,570 --> 00:17:57,960
Zhang Haixia

207
00:17:58,790 --> 00:18:00,520
has a possibility of survival.

208
00:18:03,070 --> 00:18:04,650
Strictly speaking,

209
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:06,890
he is now

210
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:08,720
between life and death.

211
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:11,390
Whether he can survive or not

212
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:15,100
depends on whether
he can enter that place.

213
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:16,920
Follow me.

214
00:18:18,380 --> 00:18:19,440
Pick up your shoes.

215
00:18:37,030 --> 00:18:39,950
The serial number of the information
in the Archives has a pattern.

216
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:41,400
The smaller the number,

217
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:43,400
the more recent it happened.

218
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,720
[Southern Archives Document]

219
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:44,960
011.

220
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,500
Is it so old?

221
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,760
In the 25th year of Daoguang,

222
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,470
weird issues happened

223
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:53,560
in many villages in Xiacheng Mountain.

224
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:55,070
[Case Closure Report]

225
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:56,950
Some villagers saw
evil spirits crawling out of the crack.

226
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:59,480
The Archives were assisting
and sent someone

227
00:18:59,690 --> 00:19:03,350
to go thousands of meters underground
through the crack of the mountain

228
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:05,600
to find a different realm underground—
the Underworld.

229
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,450
In order to protect the Underworld

230
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:09,060
to protect the people of Xiacheng,

231
00:19:09,060 --> 00:19:11,830
the Archives was built upon the Underworld

232
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,530
to prevent things inside

233
00:19:13,530 --> 00:19:14,790
from causing trouble.

234
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:19,750
But what does this have to do

235
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,920
with Shrimpie's death?

236
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,100
Keep reading.

237
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:22,660
Okay.

238
00:19:28,290 --> 00:19:31,100
The agents found a body of water

239
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:33,150
while exploring the Underworld.

240
00:19:33,660 --> 00:19:34,920
Strangely,

241
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:37,070
when an agent enters the water,

242
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,750
their body temperature will drop sharply

243
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,010
and die mysteriously.

244
00:19:46,210 --> 00:19:47,280
Later it was found

245
00:19:47,330 --> 00:19:48,750
they didn't die.

246
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:51,700
Instead, they are in
a long fake-death state

247
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:54,500
without breath or pulse.

248
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,660
A parasitic worm on them

249
00:20:00,860 --> 00:20:02,890
can remove the toxin of Haizun.

250
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,500
Just like how cows and sheep
can eat poisonous wild grass—

251
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,500
the parasitic bacteria in their stomachs

252
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,030
can help detoxify the poison.

253
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:13,560
They are both
on the same and different sides.

254
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:26,940
The Archives found that

255
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:29,980
this is a good way to escape.

256
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,460
So I made them into two kinds of medicine.

257
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:33,560
They can be used

258
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:35,790
during the most dangerous missions—

259
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:38,030
to feign death
to fool the enemies

260
00:20:38,330 --> 00:20:40,530
and bring back the secret information.

261
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,880
So Shrimpie's death is a fake one?

262
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:45,250
What about the antidote?
Why...

263
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:46,660
Why didn't he take the antidote?

264
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:49,180
Because the way to make the antidote
is very troublesome.

265
00:20:49,180 --> 00:20:51,390
And I am still short of three rare herbs.

266
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:53,000
I'll find it. Where is it?

267
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,160
In the depths of the Archives.

268
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:56,410
Depth...

269
00:20:56,670 --> 00:20:57,540
Depths?

270
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:00,340
Three years ago, when you caused
the trouble in Panhua Reef,

271
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:05,410
[Three years ago]

272
00:21:00,650 --> 00:21:02,830
people of the Archives were hunted down.

273
00:21:02,830 --> 00:21:04,460
To prevent enemy invasion,

274
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,290
I closed the Archives ahead of time

275
00:21:06,290 --> 00:21:08,750
and dismissed everyone
in the Zhang family.

276
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:13,920
[Dragon-breaking Stone mechanism]

277
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:22,820
I then turned on
all the defense mechanisms around

278
00:21:23,290 --> 00:21:24,800
to protect the Archives,

279
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,660
not allowing anyone to break into
the Archives.

280
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:30,250
But actually,

281
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:33,500
there is another secret entrance
to the Archives.

282
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:36,380
This entrance has a set
of complicated defense mechanisms

283
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:38,510
and changes its location constantly.

284
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:40,500
This mechanism was designed

285
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:43,660
by different high-ranking agents taking
different phases each over the years.

286
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:44,790
No one in the Archives

287
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:46,760
knows how to crack it completely,

288
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:47,960
including me.

289
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:55,210
The last agent
who participated in the design

290
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:56,380
was Zhang Haixia.

291
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,010
If someone can open this mechanism,

292
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:00,980
it could only be you.

293
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:06,320
So if I want to enter the Archives,

294
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,920
I have to break through
all the mechanisms.

295
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,460
In that case, Master, won't you have to—

296
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:12,460
This thing must be done by you alone.

297
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,090
I can tell you how to find the Archives.

298
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:16,610
But as to how to get in

299
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,780
and where the medicine is hidden,

300
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,360
it's up to you to find out.

301
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:24,820
[Horned Rhino] [Qilin's Blood] [Mud Wyrm]

302
00:22:23,390 --> 00:22:24,960
How long does Shrimpie have?

303
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:27,870
[Countdown: 12 hours]

304
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:26,310
12 hours.

305
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:29,180
Down to the hour?

306
00:22:30,540 --> 00:22:32,460
Haizun only appears during the blood moon.

307
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:33,640
According to my calculation,

308
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:35,270
there will be a blood moon tonight.

309
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:36,370
If you miss it,

310
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,590
I don't know when the next time will be

311
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:39,140
and whether Zhang Haixia

312
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,360
can still be saved then.

313
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:48,540
Starting now,

314
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,510
you have 12 hours.

315
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,770
Zhang Haixia's life

316
00:22:54,550 --> 00:22:55,520
is in your hands.

317
00:24:18,370 --> 00:24:19,120
Remember,

318
00:24:19,770 --> 00:24:21,230
conquer your true nature.

319
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:25,190
This is really your last chance.

320
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:56,940
[Zhang Han] [Zhang Haijiang]
[Zhang Hairong]

321
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:59,640
[Zhang Haiqi] [Zhang Haixia]
[Zhang Hailou]

322
00:25:19,690 --> 00:25:20,400
Tonight,

323
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:22,390
I will avenge all of you.

324
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:29,140
Listen.

325
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:31,660
The Archives is very large.

326
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,600
Go and ask around

327
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:35,250
the old address of the Archives

328
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:37,750
which now stands Haili Bank.

329
00:25:37,850 --> 00:25:38,700
Go check if anything odd

330
00:25:38,700 --> 00:25:40,410
has happened around the area.

331
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,440
Because the Archives' defense mechanism

332
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,730
is very special.

333
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:46,070
Maybe someone will notice something

334
00:25:46,070 --> 00:25:48,210
and help you find the entrance.

335
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:50,360
You can only rely on yourself this time.

336
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:52,550
I have something important to do.

337
00:25:53,070 --> 00:25:54,000
Come to think of it,

338
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:56,250
there were 18 bowls in total.

339
00:25:56,660 --> 00:25:57,610
Before leaving,

340
00:25:57,610 --> 00:25:59,790
the shop owner pulled Erlang's sleeve.

341
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:03,330
But the night
in Jingyang Hill was getting thicker.

342
00:26:03,330 --> 00:26:05,290
Erlang, under the influence of alcohol,

343
00:26:05,290 --> 00:26:06,420
with his bare hands—

344
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,250
Hello, everyone.

345
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:19,230
I'm the new storyteller here.

346
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:20,200
I'm new here,

347
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:22,950
so I do lack some good stories.

348
00:26:23,260 --> 00:26:25,500
So I would like to ask

349
00:26:25,530 --> 00:26:27,670
if there's anything interesting
that happened around here.

350
00:26:27,670 --> 00:26:28,730
I dare not say anything else—

351
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:30,960
but I will make sure
you have tea and snacks to your fill.

352
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:33,400
[Talking of Antiquity and Lamenting Today]

353
00:26:31,260 --> 00:26:31,860
I promise.

354
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:36,190
Just say it if
you want to listen to stories.

355
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,860
Who cares about the tea money?

356
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:39,970
What story would you want to hear?

357
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:43,070
I just want to listen to odd happenings

358
00:26:43,550 --> 00:26:45,200
in this area.

359
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,380
Odd happenings?

360
00:26:46,570 --> 00:26:48,840
What I talked about yesterday—

361
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:50,810
I have one.

362
00:26:51,290 --> 00:26:52,420
What do they know?

363
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:56,660
Do you believe

364
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:59,440
that walls can eat people?

365
00:26:59,690 --> 00:27:01,060
Really?

366
00:27:02,110 --> 00:27:03,550
Tell us.

367
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:04,380
Tell us.

368
00:27:04,380 --> 00:27:06,510
Don't talk about it. Do you want to die?

369
00:27:08,070 --> 00:27:09,030
Do you know

370
00:27:09,380 --> 00:27:11,750
Hongtou Mazu Temple?

371
00:27:14,430 --> 00:27:18,240
[Hongtou Mazu Temple]

372
00:27:15,290 --> 00:27:18,090
Hongtou Mazu Temple is a temple
of the underworld.

373
00:27:23,330 --> 00:27:25,260
When we fishermen find human bones

374
00:27:25,530 --> 00:27:27,330
when out fishing,

375
00:27:27,660 --> 00:27:30,110
we will bring them
to the temple of the underworld.

376
00:27:30,110 --> 00:27:32,510
All beings grieve for their fellow beings.

377
00:28:22,070 --> 00:28:23,330
My goodness.

378
00:28:23,330 --> 00:28:25,460
Look at how decayed
the wall is.

379
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:35,750
Immortal,

380
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:38,380
I will fix this place.

381
00:28:58,900 --> 00:29:00,270
What book is this?

382
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,140
So many cracks are drawn on it.

383
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:28,350
[Hongtou Mazu Temple]

384
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:27,850
Yet, in just a few days,

385
00:29:28,570 --> 00:29:30,640
Chen disappeared.

386
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:32,380
Well...

387
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,850
Chen died just like that.

388
00:29:54,290 --> 00:29:56,200
He stuffed himself into the wall crack

389
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:57,610
and squeezed himself to death.

390
00:29:57,610 --> 00:29:59,840
Some say the gaps are alive,

391
00:30:00,030 --> 00:30:01,150
and some say

392
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:05,140
those gaps lead to the Netherworld.

393
00:30:05,530 --> 00:30:06,920
But as to

394
00:30:07,530 --> 00:30:09,780
why the wall is eating humans

395
00:30:10,030 --> 00:30:11,570
and where it leads to—

396
00:30:12,110 --> 00:30:13,680
no one knows.

397
00:30:14,610 --> 00:30:15,960
Keep making up stories.

398
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:16,530
Yeah.

399
00:30:16,530 --> 00:30:17,920
I know Chen.

400
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,070
He's a thief.

401
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:20,290
Every time he stole something,

402
00:30:20,290 --> 00:30:20,960
he would put it in the temple.

403
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:21,660
Sir,

404
00:30:21,660 --> 00:30:23,460
you mentioned that ancient text

405
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:24,530
had a few words.

406
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:25,200
Do you remember

407
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,290
what those words were?

408
00:30:26,290 --> 00:30:28,500
It was something like...

409
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:38,780
[Southern Archives, No. 28]

410
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:39,790
something something Archives.

411
00:30:52,030 --> 00:30:54,890
[Hongtou Mazu Temple]

412
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:03,250
Hurry up!

413
00:32:02,850 --> 00:32:05,790
[Mo Faction Warlord Base, Xiacheng]

414
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:05,850
Come on.
Those at the back, keep up.

415
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,000
Okay, put it down.

416
00:32:10,330 --> 00:32:11,070
Hurry up!

417
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:11,530
Come on!

418
00:32:12,660 --> 00:32:13,630
Hurry up!

419
00:32:15,030 --> 00:32:16,310
Lift it up!

420
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:25,060
[Map of Xiacheng City]

421
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:26,500
Come in.

422
00:32:29,210 --> 00:32:31,760
[Map of Xiacheng City]

423
00:32:32,030 --> 00:32:33,570
Sir, you wanted to see me?

424
00:32:33,570 --> 00:32:36,970
Zhang Haiqi came back
posing as the daughter of the Ship King.

425
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,150
Also,

426
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:39,850
your sister Bai Zhu

427
00:32:40,030 --> 00:32:41,230
died.

428
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:46,880
[Assassin, Bai Yu]

429
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:46,610
She was killed by Zhang Haiqi

430
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:48,830
carrying out the mission on the boat.

431
00:32:51,950 --> 00:32:53,480
Did you bring her body back?

432
00:32:53,570 --> 00:32:55,560
You don't know Zhang Haiqi.

433
00:32:56,110 --> 00:32:57,970
She doesn't leave the body intact

434
00:32:59,570 --> 00:33:01,960
when killing someone.

435
00:33:18,260 --> 00:33:20,650
I missed you so much,

436
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,570
Miss Dong.

437
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,310
You're not Mo Yungao.

438
00:33:45,030 --> 00:33:46,230
Where is Zhang Haiqi?

439
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:49,400
Where is Zhang Haiqi?

440
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,310
The armory exploded!

441
00:33:53,570 --> 00:33:55,730
Sir, someone set up explosives!

442
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:03,290
Guards!

443
00:34:04,830 --> 00:34:05,880
Seal off the base immediately.

444
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:07,410
You must catch Zhang Haiqi!

445
00:34:07,420 --> 00:34:08,080
-Yes!
-Yes!

446
00:35:20,620 --> 00:35:22,160
Over there! Chase!

447
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:04,220
Zhang Haiqi!

448
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,310
Sir,

449
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:37,530
Commander sent an emergency telegram.

450
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:38,390
Read it.

451
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:44,430
I heard that

452
00:37:44,460 --> 00:37:46,870
Zhang Haiqi pretended
to be the daughter of the Ship King,

453
00:37:46,870 --> 00:37:48,140
Miss Dong,

454
00:37:48,170 --> 00:37:49,770
and has returned to Xiacheng.

455
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:52,560
This is due to your negligence.

456
00:37:52,950 --> 00:37:55,380
We must capture Zhang Haiqi,

457
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,060
the location of the Archives,

458
00:37:57,310 --> 00:38:00,040
and obtain related files
of the patriarch of the Zhang family.

459
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:02,130
If you fail your mission again,

460
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:03,760
you...

461
00:38:04,860 --> 00:38:07,310
you shall die as an apology.

462
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:24,880
Pass my order.

463
00:38:26,190 --> 00:38:28,380
Take the rest of the equipment

464
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:29,860
to the Dong Residence.

465
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:36,560
I don't believe we can't catch
Zhang Haiqi.
